{
  "card_id": "reversal_setup",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "Reversal Setup",
  "aliases": [
    "Daily Reversal",
    "Reversal Day"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A daily framework where price opens, trades into the previous day's high or low, forms a shallow wick at that level, and reverses back into the range, confirmed by a lower time frame change in state of delivery, targeting the previous day's equilibrium or fair value gaps.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Frame the setup off the previous day's high (for bearish reversal) or previous day's low (for bullish reversal) as the important level.",
    "Price must open and trade directly into that previous day high/low first (open-high sequence for bearish, open-low sequence for bullish).",
    "A shallow wick must form at the previous day high/low; a large wick instead requires waiting for candle 3 continuation rather than trading the reversal.",
    "Require a lower time frame change in state of delivery to confirm the higher time frame wick — hourly or 30-minute for Asia/London, 5-minute or 15-minute for New York.",
    "Optional confirmation: SMT divergence with a correlated asset (e.g. DXY) at the swept level.",
    "Targets are set to the previous day's EQ (equilibrium) or fair value gaps within the previous day's range, with the previous day's opposite extreme as an extended target."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Used to fade extensions into the prior day's range extremes after liquidity is swept. Entry is taken on the lower time frame CISD confirming the daily wick; stops sit beyond the swept high/low. First target is EQ of the previous day's range, with fair value gaps inside the range as additional objectives. Best executed when a higher time frame bias supports the reversal direction rather than pattern-trading in isolation.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Pattern-trading the reversal without aligning it with a higher time frame bias.",
    "Taking the reversal when the wick at the previous day high/low is large — a large wick does not support immediate expansion and requires waiting for candle 3.",
    "Treating a protected swing formed during the move as permanently protected; once it hits liquidity it can be swept before the true move."
  ],
